{"Given some categorized constants in the form \"category: constant_1; constant_2; ...; constant_n\" and some predicates about the relation among different categories of constants, write ASP (Answer Set Programming) rules to generate the search space of possible relations. In your response, include a SINGLE ASP code-block with the rules - it will be automatically parsed from your response.\n\nConstants:\nemployee: \"Bonita\"; \"Yvette\"; \"Tabitha\".\nprice: 225; 275; 325.\nwood_type: \"ash\"; \"poplar\"; \"sandalwood\".\n\nPredicates:\n% The categories include employee, price, and wood_type. We use different variables E, P, and W to represent employee, price, and wood_type.\n% We match an employee E with price P and wood type W, where E belongs to employee, P belongs to price, and W belongs to wood_type.\nmatch(E, P, W)\n\nASP Rules:\n```asp\n% Define the constants in each category.\nemployee(\"Bonita\"; \"Yvette\"; \"Tabitha\").\nprice(225; 275; 325).\nwood_type(\"ash\"; \"poplar\"; \"sandalwood\").\n\n% For each employee E, it matches with exactly 1 price P and 1 wood type W.\n{match(E, P, W): price(P), wood_type(W)}=1 :- employee(E).\n```\n\nConstants:\nclients: \"Aimee\"; \"Ginger\"; \"Freda\"; \"Hannah\".  \nprice: 150; 160; 170; 180.  \nmasseuse: \"Lynda\"; \"Nancy\"; \"Teri\"; \"Whitney\".\n\nPredicates:\nschedule(Client, Masseuse, Price)\n\nASP Rules:": "```asp\n% Define the constants in each category.\nclients(\"Aimee\"; \"Ginger\"; \"Freda\"; \"Hannah\").\nprice(150; 160; 170; 180).\nmasseuse(\"Lynda\"; \"Nancy\"; \"Teri\"; \"Whitney\").\n\n% For each client, there is exactly one masseuse and one price assigned.\n{schedule(Client, Masseuse, Price): masseuse(Masseuse), price(Price)}=1 :- clients(Client).\n```", "Given some categorized constants in the form \"category: constant_1; constant_2; ...; constant_n\" and some predicates about the relation among different categories of constants, write ASP (Answer Set Programming) rules to generate the search space of possible relations. In your response, include a SINGLE ASP code-block with the rules - it will be automatically parsed from your response.\n\nConstants:\nemployee: \"Bonita\"; \"Yvette\"; \"Tabitha\".\nprice: 225; 275; 325.\nwood_type: \"ash\"; \"poplar\"; \"sandalwood\".\n\nPredicates:\n% The categories include employee, price, and wood_type. We use different variables E, P, and W to represent employee, price, and wood_type.\n% We match an employee E with price P and wood type W, where E belongs to employee, P belongs to price, and W belongs to wood_type.\nmatch(E, P, W)\n\nASP Rules:\n```asp\n% Define the constants in each category.\nemployee(\"Bonita\"; \"Yvette\"; \"Tabitha\").\nprice(225; 275; 325).\nwood_type(\"ash\"; \"poplar\"; \"sandalwood\").\n\n% For each employee E, it matches with exactly 1 price P and 1 wood type W.\n{match(E, P, W): price(P), wood_type(W)}=1 :- employee(E).\n```\n\nConstants:\ndiplomat: \"Gilbert\"; \"Macdonald\"; \"Pickett\"; \"Vasquez\".  \nmonth: 1; 2; 3; 4.  \nduration: 4; 5; 9; 10.\n\nPredicates:\nassign(D, M, Dur)\n\nASP Rules:": "```asp\n% Define the constants in each category.\ndiplomat(\"Gilbert\"; \"Macdonald\"; \"Pickett\"; \"Vasquez\").\nmonth(1; 2; 3; 4).\nduration(4; 5; 9; 10).\n\n% For each diplomat D, assign exactly 1 month M and 1 duration Dur.\n{assign(D, M, Dur): month(M), duration(Dur)}=1 :- diplomat(D).\n```", "Given some categorized constants in the form \"category: constant_1; constant_2; ...; constant_n\" and some predicates about the relation among different categories of constants, write ASP (Answer Set Programming) rules to generate the search space of possible relations. In your response, include a SINGLE ASP code-block with the rules - it will be automatically parsed from your response.\n\nConstants:\nemployee: \"Bonita\"; \"Yvette\"; \"Tabitha\".\nprice: 225; 275; 325.\nwood_type: \"ash\"; \"poplar\"; \"sandalwood\".\n\nPredicates:\n% The categories include employee, price, and wood_type. We use different variables E, P, and W to represent employee, price, and wood_type.\n% We match an employee E with price P and wood type W, where E belongs to employee, P belongs to price, and W belongs to wood_type.\nmatch(E, P, W)\n\nASP Rules:\n```asp\n% Define the constants in each category.\nemployee(\"Bonita\"; \"Yvette\"; \"Tabitha\").\nprice(225; 275; 325).\nwood_type(\"ash\"; \"poplar\"; \"sandalwood\").\n\n% For each employee E, it matches with exactly 1 price P and 1 wood type W.\n{match(E, P, W): price(P), wood_type(W)}=1 :- employee(E).\n```\n\nConstants:\nnames: \"Cornick\"; \"Dreadco\"; \"Foltron\"; \"Worul\".  \nmonths: 1; 2; 3; 4.  \ncompanies: \"Permias\"; \"Rubicorp\"; \"Techtrin\"; \"Ubersplore\".\n\nPredicates:\nlaunches(C, N, M)\n\nASP Rules:": "```asp\n% Define the constants in each category.\nnames(\"Cornick\"; \"Dreadco\"; \"Foltron\"; \"Worul\").\nmonths(1; 2; 3; 4).\ncompanies(\"Permias\"; \"Rubicorp\"; \"Techtrin\"; \"Ubersplore\").\n\n% For each company C, it launches exactly one name N and one month M.\n{launches(C, N, M): names(N), months(M)}=1 :- companies(C).\n```"}